2.20	Paul_H._Harvey	Paul H. Harvey	Paul H. Harvey CBE FRS (born 19 January 1947) is a British evolutionary biologist. He is Professor of Zoology and was head of the zoology department at Oxford University from 1998 - 2011, holding these posts in conjunction with a professorial fellowship at Jesus College, Oxford. He was elected to the Fellowship of the Royal Society in 1992. In 1997 Harvey was awarded the NAS Award for Scientific Reviewing from the National Academy of Sciences. He was the Secretary of the Zoological Society of London.	
